Go to Horizon using firefox from host
On the dashboard, 

Go to Data Processing --> Clusters --> Image Registry
You should see the image you registered in the last step. Ensure it has correct tags and save

Go to Data Processing --> Clusters --> Node Group Template --> Create Template
Enter following variables and create a master node group template
--plugin vanilla 
--plugin-version 2.7.1
--name vanilla-default-master 
--processes namenode resourcemanager 
--flavor m1.medium
--auto-security-group
--floating-ip-pool

Go to Data Processing --> Clusters --> Node Group Template --> Create Template
Enter following variables and create a worker node group template
--plugin vanilla 
--plugin-version 2.7.1
--name vanilla-default-worker 
--processes datanode nodemanager 
--flavor m1.medium
--auto-security-group
--floating-ip-pool

Go to Data Processing --> Clusters --> Cluster Template --> Create Template
Enter following variables and create a cluster template
--name vanilla-default-cluster 
--node-groups vanilla-default-master:1 vanilla-default-worker:3

Go to Data Processing --> Clusters --> Launch Cluster
Enter following variables and launch a cluster template
--name myCluster
--cluster-template vanilla-default-cluster
--user-keypair my_stack
--neutron-network private
--image sahara-vanilla-latest-ubuntu
